title: For Sale/Trade:  Daewoo DR200 with Beta Drum, Mags, Ammo
postcontent:
I am selling my Daewoo DR-200.  This was not an easy decision, but while it is a fantastic rifle and an excellent SHTF weapon choice, I simply do not LIKE it enough.  I am not a soldier, and I want a gun I enjoy shooting, carrying, and looking at - and I've found that I am a huge fan of pistols and pistol-caliber carbines.  So, I'm selling this to have some extra funds to look at other options - I'll probably just get another Cx4, I absolutely loved that gun while I had it.  On the upside, this is not money that might be needed for my upcoming move - I am selling this gun for the sole purpose of BUYING guns.  Should be fun.

This rifle is in excellent condition, and works flawlessly.  It has a 20" barrel unmodified from when it was imported (still has the silver-soldered false flash hider).  It has OEM handguards, a Stormwerkz super-low top rail for mounting optics, a side-folding stock and a Troy Battle-Ax CQB grip.  This grip is awesome, it looks short but with the receiver attachment it ends up being about the same length as an A2 grip but much more comfy.  One thing of note, the rifle loves green-follower mags.  It will work fine with any AR magazine, but I have found that the green-followers are easy to load on a closed bolt with a full 30-round load, whereas tan follower mags and PMags are a bit stiff on a closed bolt (when I had PMags I left them one round short).  All mags I've tested will load and function fine, I just went with these because they worked so well in that specific use case.

This will be sold ONLY as a package, including the weapon, an A2 grip so you have options, four GI green-follower mags loaded with 55gr. FMJ ammo (I also added a paracord loop on the floorplates of these ones), a Beta C-Mag loaded with 100 rounds of 55gr. FMJ ammo (complete with pouch and lube), and a "fat-fiddy" ammo can loaded up with 18 GI green-follower mags (all empty).

The rifle will not include the Izzy sling, I'm hanging onto that to stick on whatever I settle on for my personal rifle/carbine/PDW choice.  Go buy one though, they're really nice slings if you just want something functional without too many bells and whistles.

$1400 or best offer (seriously...send me offers), only trade I'll look at will involve a Beretta Cx4 carbine in 9x19mm OR a FN PS90 with the USG optic (preferably the OD stock), OR a Colt Anaconda with a 6" barrel.  I am not looking at anything else right now while I think about my options.

(The pics show it with the A2 grip installed, if you wanna see pics with the other stuff just ask)

title: For Sale:  Remington 700 SPS Tactical .308 (super accurate)
postcontent: I have decided to sell my Remington 700 SPS Tactical in .308.  This is another one I can tell I'm going to miss, but I'm trying to thin the collection and free up some cash for a M1a, M14, LaRue OBR, Sako TRG or FNH bolt gun.  She is topped off with Leupold bases and rings but I couldn't tell you what kind of scope I have on her right now.  I picked the scope up for cheap from a friend, all I know is that it really does get the job done (my plan was to eventually replace it with a Leupold MK4 when I had the cash).  Anyway, I pretty much just finished the barrel break in on this one and she is a real tack driver.  My break in procedure went as followes: 3 single shots with a cool down period and cleaning between each, then 4 - 3 shot groups with a cool and clean between each group, then I end with a 5 shot group for a total of 20 rounds.  That's all I've shot out of her yet.  I didn't measure any of the groups because I was starting to play around with loadings but I can tell you that this rifle does love 168gr Sierra Match boat tail bullets.  She shoots super tight with them.  The bi-pod isn't included in the rifle sale as it will be put on my next purchase (from the list above) when I get the cash.  Not to worry, there are bipods all over for cheap now.  Hopefully I'll hear from you soon, lets make a deal!

title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec PLR-16 Hunting/Silhouette Pistol
postcontent:
PLR-16
The PLR-16 is a gas operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in 5.56 mm NATO caliber. It is intended to be the ideal Silhouette shooting and hunting pistol. The rifling is 1 turn in 9 inches, right hand twist. The PLR-16 has a conventional, long-stroke gas-piston operation and utilizes the proven Johnson/Stoner breech locking system. The rear sight is adjustable for windage. The front sight is similar to an AR-15 style rifle, and adjustable for elevation. An integrated MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail will accept a multitude of standard accessories. The muzzle is threaded 1/2-28 TPI to accept standard attachments such as a muzzle brake or flash hider. Except for the barrel, bolt, sights, and mechanism, the PLR-16 pistol is made entirely of high-impact glass fiber reinforced polymer.
